   If you like Bed, you may also like:
     * [a0977462521_9.jpg]
       The Nearest Exit
       by Memory Drawings
       supported by 4 fans who also own “The music of chance”
       I keep going back and listening to this new disc by Memory
       Drawings, as it is all kinds of wonderful. Entirely instrumental,
       it features gorgeous hammered dulcimer and aching violins, and is a
       blend of ethereal sounds and dreamy orchestral passages with
       elements of ambient and shoegaze. It keeps hooking me in and
       drawing me back; this is an incredibly passionately emotive and
       meditative jewel. Eve McGivern
       go to album
     * [a3449011794_9.jpg]
       Crush
       by Fielded
       Airbrushed synthpop from New York sound artist Fielded is equal
       parts deep emotion and high fashion style. Bandcamp New & Notable
       Sep 26, 2019
       go to album
     * [a0311616894_9.jpg]
       Nuits Plurielles
       by Bronswick
       Slick, swooning Francophone pop from the Montreal duo, tailor-made
       for creatures of the night. Bandcamp New & Notable Sep 25, 2019
       go to album
     * [a1442838953_9.jpg]
       Be Lucky
       by Penny Police
       Marie Fjeltsted's latest art-pop creation is forward-thinking but
       accessible, intimate but luxuriously detailed. Bandcamp New &
       Notable Sep 24, 2019
       go to album
     * [a2713634728_9.jpg]
       Peace Process
       by Run Child Run
       On his latest, Ian Sims seeks healing in the aftermath of a
       breakup. Bandcamp Album of the Day Sep 20, 2019
       go to album
     * [a2461113377_9.jpg]
       Fruit (EP)
       by Sharky
       The UK act Sharky writes drifting, dreamlike songs that stretch
       gentle, upper-register vocals over a bed of gurgling synths.
       Bandcamp New & Notable Sep 7, 2019
       go to album
     * [a3415731328_9.jpg]
       Hip Happiness
       by The Plastic Shoelaces
       Two tracks of amazing jangle pop that are instantly recognizable as
       the work of Sacramento indie legend Scott Miller. Bandcamp New &
       Notable Aug 29, 2019
       go to album

